results.description:
A Marvel NOW! title starring the Merc with a Mouth named Deadpool! Written by comedians Brian Posehn and Gerry Duggan. The comic was a direct continuation of Deadpool Vol.2. Follow Deadpool as he makes new friends and even gets married! The series lasted until issue 45 (or 250 in Deadpool logic) and ended due to the events of Secret Wars. It was replaced by the Secret Wars tie-in series Mrs. Deadpool and the Howling Commandos before Deadpool Volume 4 was started.

Artists

  • Tony Moore (#1 - 6)
  • Scott Koblish (#7,13 -14, 20, 26, 28, 34)
  • Mike Hawthorne (#8 - 12, 21 - 25, 35 - )
  • Declan Shalvey (#15 - 19)
  • John Lucas (#29 - #33)

Trade Paperbacks

  • Vol. 1: Dead Presidents (#1-6)
  • Deadpool Firsts (#1)
  • Deadpool by Posehn & Duggan: The Complete Collection Vol. 1 (#1-14, 20 & 26)
  • Vol. 2: Soul Hunter (#7-12)
  • Deadpool Flashbacks (#7, 13, 20, 26, 34, 40 & 250)
  • Spider-Man/Deadpool: Don't Call It A Team-Up (#10)
  • Vol. 3: The Good, the Bad and the Ugly (#13-19)
  • Deadpool by Posehn & Duggan: The Complete Collection Vol. 2 (#15-19 & 21-25)
  • Vol. 4: Deadpool Vs. S.H.I.E.L.D. (#20-25)
  • Vol. 5: The Wedding of Deadpool (#26-28)
  • Deadpool by Posehn & Duggan: The Complete Collection Vol. 3 (#27-34)
  • Vol. 6: Original Sin (#29-34)
  • Vol. 7: AXIS (#35-40)
  • Vol. 8: All Good Things (#41-44 and 45 (250))

Hardcover Collections

  • Deadpool by Posehn And Duggan vol. 1 (#1-12)
  • Deadpool By Posehn & Duggan Omnibus (#1-45)
  • Deadpool by Posehn And Duggan vol. 2 (#13-25)
  • Deadpool: The Adamantium Collection (#15-19)
  • Deadpool by Posehn And Duggan vol. 3 (#26-34)
  • Original Sin Companion (#29-34)
  • Deadpool by Posehn And Duggan vol. 4 (#35-45 (250))
